1.  What is Maven?
Ans) Maven is a powerful project management tool that is based on POM (project object model).  It is used fo projects build, dependency and documentation.
Maven compile the code, test the code, validate the code and package the code.

Maven type--Java based build tool.
Vendor--Apache
Is open source--yes
version--3.52
Is executable software?--No, download as zip, extract and use it.


2.  What is the difference between ANT and Maven?
Ans) 1.  ANT scripts are not reusable and Maven plugins are reusable.
2.  ANT is less preferred than.  Maven is more preferred than ANT.
3.  ANT is a build tool and Maven project management tool.
